</IN>
<LP>
   Allou Health &amp; Beauty Care Inc. reported fiscal
first-quarter earnings rose 14% as quarterly sales reached a
record.
   The distributor of health and beauty aids posted
first-quarter earnings of $268,738, or 10 cents a share,
compared with $235,437, or nine cents a share, the year
