<HL>
   International Brief -- Oakbridge Ltd.:
   Australian Firm Posts Surge
   In Operating Profit for Year
</HL>
<DATE>
08/31/90
</DATE>
<SO>
WALL STREET JOURNAL (J), NO PAGE CITATION
</SO>
<CO>
   A.OAK
</CO>
<IN>
EARNINGS (ERN)
</IN>
<LP>
   Australian coal miner Oakbridge Ltd. reported that
operating profit for the fiscal year ended June 30 soared to
42.7 million Australian dollars (US$35.5 million) from A$3.4
million a year earlier.
   Oakbridge attributed the sharp increase to a restructuring
of the company and rationalization of its assets, including
the acquisition of the Australian coal-mining assets of
Elders Resources NZFP Ltd. at June 30, 1989.
</LP>
<TEXT>
   Firmer coal prices and a favorable exchange rate also
boosted profit.
   Total operating revenue jumped to A$428.6 million from
A$108.9 million, as sales revenue quadrupled to A$397.9
million from A$100 million.
   Oakbridge posted an operating profit before tax and
abnormal items of A$25.8 million, up 659% from A$3.4 million.
   It said an abnormal profit of A$25.2 million came from the
sale of 20% of the assets of the Clarence Colliery and from a
pension-fund surplus. Last year Oakbridge reported no
abnormal profits.
